Colour (
Fig. 3
): Head, thorax, and abdomen black; pronotum with transverse, orange mark near anterior margin; distal parts of all acetabula yellowish. Antenna black, basal third (or little less) of antennomere 1 yellow. Legs chiefly black, often with weak bluish or greenish shimmer; pro- and metacoxae, pro- and metatrochanters yellow; base of profemur yellow, but on dorsal surface, close to flexor side, with black or brown stripe that reaches base in most specimens.

Genital segments small and weakly modified. Pygophore subovate. Proctiger (
Fig. 14
) with well developed, broad lateral lobes, sclerotized part slightly broader than long. Paramere (
Fig. 17
) small, with a moderately wide basal part, then suddenly narrowed to a slender, sickle-shaped, dorsally curved distal part; apex narrowly rounded.
